The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Emami numbers shine
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Emami numbers shine
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 28: Emami Ltd, the FMCG company of the Emami group, has posted a significant jump in consolidated profit after tax for 2007-08 at Rs 91.26 crore against Rs 66.2 crore in the previous fiscal.        
	Despite appreciation of the rupee against the dollar by around 14 per cent, the international business has grown 12 per cent in the year and West Asia and Africa are the primary contributors to the growth.         
	While the company continues to explore new markets, the thrust is on increasing distribution and penetration in existing markets and developing itself as a global brand.         
	The companys Boroplus antiseptic cream is the largest selling ointment in India as well as Ukraine, Russia and Nepal.         
	Emamis sales grew to Rs 618.03 crore in the reporting period from Rs 518.26 crore a year ago.        
	The company will focus on rural marketing strategy this year, which includes sales through mobile traders and small village shops.                                                                                                                                                   
